Let me carefully define the vertices and blocks ensuring each hex follows the right-hand rule convention (vertices ordered so the block interior is on the left when looking from vertex 0→1→2→3 toward vertex 4→5→6→7).

Key principle: For `hex (v0 v1 v2 v3 v4 v5 v6 v7)`, the face (v0,v1,v2,v3) must have normals pointing outward/away from the block, meaning the block extends from the plane of (v0-v1-v2-v3) toward (v4-v5-v6-v7).

